@context: Demonstrates @var: static variables and CALL PYTHON ... into {var} dynamic variables
@title: demo-vars

# ── Static variables ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Declare test data once at the top; reference via {placeholder} anywhere below.
@var: {search_query} = autonomous browser testing
@var: {expected_text} = autonomous

STEP 1: Search with static variable
NAVIGATE to https://duckduckgo.com
Fill 'Search' field with '{search_query}'
PRESS ENTER
VERIFY that '{expected_text}' is present.

STEP 2: Capture dynamic variable
# CALL PYTHON ... into {var} captures the function's return value at runtime.
# The helper below lives in tests/helpers/demo_api.py and returns a fixed OTP.
CALL PYTHON helpers.demo_api.get_demo_otp into {otp}
# {otp} is now available for substitution in any subsequent step, e.g.:
# Fill 'OTP Code' field with '{otp}'
DONE.
